text: Have been patronising this stall for a long time. Food quality is good and service is excellent. Highly recommend the lemon butter grilled fish, fried spring chicken, and baked rice.

Stall : Char Grill Bar.
@ Coffeeshop : “Meet Up @ 203”, Blk 203 Hougang Street 21.

Alighted pax across the street at Kovan Residence and decided to come here for my favourite Steak 🥩: Prime Striploin steak of 200gm w/ Black Pepper sauce of Medium Rare w/ 2 side dishes : Onion Rings + Baked Potatoes 🥔 @ $12.80.

What’s so good 😊?
It’s sizzling sound as it’s served on Hotplate and upsized sauces as per requested and bottom w/ raw onions 🧅!

Onions as base to reduce the heat from the Hotplate to prevent over done ✅! But still it’s already near done … 😅😜

Always ❤️ this Char Grill Bar of this outlet that serves the better steak 🥩 w/ black pepper sauce ! 😮 🤩 ⭐️ 👍

It’s TGIF Cheers 🥂

Good good quality with cheap price. Ordered their signature Char-Grilled Chicken chop for $6.90, there are 2 side dishes you can choose out of 11 options which I like the most,plus the vegetables are all fresh.
Also,they provide cutlery in a basket with a tissue paper on it.
Definitely my first choice of western food in Singapore.

Fried rice with pork chop is reasonable. But i like pork chop with the 2 sides dishes. Mutton has shrunk is size
Easy to find table at this kopitiam
My favorite go to place for Western food! The chargrilled chicken chop is tender and juicy and the accompanying 2 side dishes are also good. Value for money neighborhood place!
